# Project Structure

**Single source of truth:** `.ai/`

| Directory | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `.ai/agents/` | Agnostic role definitions (YAML) |
| `.ai/agents/stacks/<stack>/` | Stack-specific roles (Rails = reference) |
| `.ai/skills/` | Reusable capabilities |
| `.ai/workflows/` | End-to-end processes |
| `.ai/standards/` | Agnostic engineering rules |
| `.ai/standards/stacks/<stack>/` | Stack-specific standards (Rails = reference) |
| `.ai/templates/` | Document templates |

**Multi-stack:** the agnostic core lives at the root of `.ai/standards/` and
`.ai/agents/`; language-specific guidance lives under `stacks/<stack>/`. To add a
language, see `docs/ADDING-A-LANGUAGE.md` and the `stacks/_TEMPLATE/` skeletons.

**Adapters (do not duplicate content):**
- `.cursor/rules/` → references `.ai/standards/`
- `.claude/` → Claude Code integration

**Collaboration:** `.ai/standards/collaboration.md` — Question → Options → Decision → Draft → Approval

When implementing features, follow `.ai/workflows/new-feature.yaml`.
